@rabbah IMHO I think we should make the `openwhisk-catalog` smaller not bigger.
I think we should create a `openwhisk-package-couchdb` repo and put the package content that allows users to use coucdb or cloudant with the package, and corresponding docs for that package live in the same repo.

Since this is not available yet, then I want to remove references to content that is not public yet.

> If we remove the cloudant bits which show off how to use packages, we will need to replace them with new samples.

@rabbah What specific text or usage of packages you think we are loosing?
how to use packages is already covered in [docs/packages.md](https://github.com/openwhisk/openwhisk/blob/master/docs/packages.md)

(accidentally closed.)

@mdeuser @dubeejw why is the go CLI output different for the activation record?
the dictionary is unsorted and there are keys missing.
